{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("MS13", true) >= 10 and get_quest_stage("MS13", true) < 100 %}
* Gerdur has noticed the commotion at the Riverwood Trader after their golden claw was stolen. The theft is concerning as it's the most valuable item in town and suggests bandits are getting bolder in the area.
{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("MS13", false) >= 100 %}
* Gerdur has heard from townsfolk that { player.name } recovered the golden claw stolen from the Riverwood Trader. She appreciates anyone who helps maintain order in her town, especially with the civil war stretching guard resources thin.
{# This is permanently relevant as it affects Gerdur's perception of the player as someone who helps her town #}
{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("CW01B", true) >= 1 or get_quest_stage("CW02B", true) >= 10 %}
* Gerdur is quietly proud to hear from her brother that { player.name } is joining the Stormcloak cause. She sees this as further validation of her belief that true Nords must stand against Imperial oppression.
{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("CWObj", false) >= 255 and get_civil_war_side() == "Stormcloak" %}
* Gerdur celebrates the Stormcloak victory in the civil war, feeling vindicated in her support for Ulfric. She speaks more openly about her political views now and has plans for how Riverwood might prosper in an independent Skyrim.
