{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("CWObj", false) >= 255 and get_civil_war_side() == "Imperial" %}
* Gerdur maintains a stoic demeanor despite the Imperial victory in the civil war. She worries about her brother Ralof's fate and quietly continues to hold her Stormcloak sympathies, though she's careful about expressing them openly now.
{# This is permanently relevant as it represents a major political change affecting Gerdur's daily life and business #}
{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("MQ104", true) >= 80 %}
* Gerdur has heard alarming reports about a dragon attack at the Western Watchtower near Whiterun. She's organizing Riverwood's emergency preparations, fearing their wooden buildings would be especially vulnerable to dragon fire.
{% endif %}

{% if get_quest_stage("MQ104", false) >= 160 %}
* Gerdur has heard from travelers that { player.name } helped slay a dragon outside Whiterun and absorbed its power. While skeptical of such fantastic tales, she remembers { player.name }'s connection to Helgen and wonders if there might be truth to the rumors of a Dragonborn.
{# This is permanently relevant as it establishes the player's growing reputation that would reach even small towns #}
{% endif %}
{% endblock %}